    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>127100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀλκίβιος"><unclear>Ἀ</unclear>λκίβιο<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></name></persName>
                            <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Βουλίας"><unclear>Β</unclear>ουλία<unclear>ς</unclear></name></persName><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Alkibios <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Boulias <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Alkibios <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Boulias <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Alkibios <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Boulias <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This fragment is probably the end of a list of names, which were plausibly followed by the fathers' names.</p>
                <p>A very faint angular trace at the end of line 2 shows that the last letter was a sigma, leading to read a nominative and helping to date the lettering.</p>
	           <p>Whereas Alkibios was already attested once at Cyrene, the name Boulias is new in the region and the vocalism <foreign xml:lang="grc">ου</foreign>
	              in the first syllable shows a foreign influence, as opposed to dialectal <foreign xml:lang="frc">ω</foreign>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
